TY  - JOUR
T1  - Integrating Replenishment Decisions with Advance Demand Information
AU  - Gallego, Guillermo
AU  - Özer, Özalp
Y1  - 2001/10/01
PY  - 2001
DA  - 2001/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.47.10.1344.10261
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.47.10.1344.10261
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1344
EP  - 1360
VL  - 47
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - There is a growing consensus that a portfolio of customers with different demand lead times can lead to higher, more regular revenues and better capacity utilization. Customers with positive demand lead times place orders in advance of their needs, resulting in advance demand information. This gives rise to the problem of finding effective inventory control policies under advance demand information. We show that state-dependent (s, S) and base-stock policies are optimal for stochastic inventory systems with and without fixed costs. The state of the system reflects our knowledge of advance demand information. We also determine conditions under which advance demand information has no operational value. A numerical study allows us to obtain additional insights and to evaluate strategies to induce advance demand information.
AB  - There is a growing consensus that a portfolio of customers with different demand lead times can lead to higher, more regular revenues and better capacity utilization. Customers with positive demand lead times place orders in advance of their needs, resulting in advance demand information. This gives rise to the problem of finding effective inventory control policies under advance demand information. We show that state-dependent (s, S) and base-stock policies are optimal for stochastic inventory systems with and without fixed costs. The state of the system reflects our knowledge of advance demand information. We also determine conditions under which advance demand information has no operational value. A numerical study allows us to obtain additional insights and to evaluate strategies to induce advance demand information.
